and:
The translation for "and" appears in the [[Special:Version]] page, between the last two items of a list. If a comma is needed, add it at the beginning without a gap between it and the '''<code>&amp;#32;</code>''' is a blank space, one character long, as a numeric character entity reference (in order to avoid its automatic removal at start of the wikipage). Please leave it as it is (this does '''not''' imply any semicolon punctuation), or remove the whole sequence completely in languages that don't use a leading space.

This can also appear in the credits page if the credits feature is enabled,for example [{{canonicalurl:Support|action=credits}} the credits of the support page]. (To view any credits page type <nowiki>&action=credits</nowiki> at the end of any URL in the address bar.)
